      <hr />
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <div class="definition">
         <div>
            <p>Explanatory text and the headings referred to when the linking relationship between
               headings from different subject heading systems or thesauri cannot be adequately
               conveyed by fields 700-785. No subelements of the <em>heading referred to</em> are
            separately subfield coded. Adjacent headings referred to may be contained in a single
            subfield $a. The heading referred to may be an established heading or a
            subject subdivision that is not equivalent to but is related to the heading in the 1XX
            field.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div>
            <p>For example, the heading referred to may be restricted to being used as a subdivision
               in
               the related subject heading system/thesaurus, or, the related subject heading
               system/thesaurus may require the use of more than one heading to equal the concept
               expressed by the heading in the 1XX field of the record.
            </p>
            <p>A link display may be generated from the 1XX field and field 788 in a record. The
               1XX
               field contains the <em>heading referred from</em>. Field 788 contains the explanatory
            text for the reference and the other headings referred to. Subfield $w/0 in
            any related 700-785 field(s) in the record contains code b (Link not displayed, field
            788 used).
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <div class="guidelines">
         <h4><span class="box">â </span> INDICATORS
         </h4>
         <div class="indicators">
            <div class="indicator">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>First Indicator - Undefined</strong></p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Undefined and contains a blank (#).</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicator">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>Second Indicator - Thesaurus</strong></p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Description of the second indicator is given in the <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ad7xx.html">7XX Heading Linking EntriesâGeneral Information</a></em> section.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <h4><span class="box">â </span> SUBFIELD CODES
         </h4>
         <div class="subfields">
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$a - Heading referred to</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Heading from another thesaurus to which the heading in field 1XX of the record
                        refers.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$i - Explanatory text</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Text that describes the relationship between the heading referred to in subfield
                  $a and the 1XX heading. The text may be broken up by subfield
                  $a data and may be only a connector term such as <em>and</em>. 
                        See also "Relationship information" described in
                           <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ad7xx.html">7XX Heading Linking EntriesâGeneral Information</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$2 - Source of heading or term</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Description of subfield $2 is given in the <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ad7xx.html">7XX Heading Linking EntriesâGeneral Information</a></em> section.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$4 - Relationship code</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>Description of subfield $4 is given in the <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ad7xx.html">7XX Heading Linking EntriesâGeneral Information</a></em> section.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$5 - Institution to which field applies</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="subfield">
               <div>
                  <p class="label"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
                  </p>
                  <div>
                     <p>See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ecadcntf.html">Control Subfields</a></em>.
                     </p>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <h4><span class="box">â  </span> EXAMPLES
         </h4>
         <div class="examplesec">
            <div class="example">
               <p class="exampleCaption"><em>Same term used as established heading and as subject subdivision by different thesauri:</em></p>
               <table>
                  <tr>
                     <td>008/09</td>
                     <td colspan="9">a<em><span><br /><span>[established heading record] </span></span></em></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td>008/11</td>
                     <td colspan="9">a<em><span><br /><span>[code indicating MeSH] </span></span></em></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td>150</td>
                     <td colspan="9">##$aForeign Bodies</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td>780</td>
                     <td colspan="9">#0$w#$xForeign bodies [LCSH subdivision] </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td><strong>788</strong></td>
                     <td colspan="9"><strong>#0</strong><strong>$i</strong>subdivision<strong>$a</strong>Foreign bodies<strong>$i</strong>under names of organs, e.g.<strong>$a</strong>Eye-Foreign bodies
                     </td>
                  </tr>
               </table>
            </div>
            <div class="example">
               <p class="exampleCaption"><em>Two established heading terms in one thesaurus are equivalent to one established heading
                     in another thesaurus:</em></p>
               <table>
                  <tr>
                     <td>008/09</td>
                     <td colspan="9">a<em><span><br /><span>[established heading record] </span></span></em></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td>008/11</td>
                     <td colspan="9">a<em><span><br /><span>[code indicating LCSH] </span></span></em></td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td>150</td>
                     <td colspan="9">##$aFurniture$zChina</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td>450</td>
                     <td colspan="9">##$aFurniture, Chinese</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td>750</td>
                     <td colspan="9">#7$81$wb$aChinese$2aat</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td>750</td>
                     <td colspan="9">#7$81$wb$afurniture$2aat</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td><strong>788</strong></td>
                     <td colspan="9"><strong>#7</strong><strong>$i</strong>terms<strong>$a</strong>Chinese<strong>$i</strong>and<strong>$a</strong>Furniture<strong>$i</strong>are separate facets.<strong>$2</strong>aat
                     </td>
                  </tr>
               </table>
            </div>
         </div>
      </div>
